1. Boil hakka noodles, strain and cool.
2. Sprinkle flour on it and deep fry in oil.
3. Chop onions, tomato, green chillies and carrot.
4. Add the chopped vegetables to the noodles and mix.
5. Add red chilli powder, salt, ketchup, tamarind chutney, pudina chutney and little sugar. Mix and Chinese Bhel is ready to be served!